name: Mahakali
description:
Mahakali is the Hindu Goddess of time and death, considered the consort of Mahakala, the god of consciousness, the basis of reality and existence.
Mahakali is a form of Adi parashakti, which is beyond space and time. Kali is Adi parashakti's anger power. She is the greatest aspect of Kali that many Hindus hold as the Divine Mother.
